---<br>
This in all practicality never ever happens. I have searched through my logs and have found a few places where I fumble myself, but not once where my target fumbles, and I do have a lot of log files.<br>
<br>
We already have a frontal and side style, so either a low fatigue use anytime style, or a use from behind style would be useful for an axe user.<br>
---<br>
<br>
(21) Valkyrie's Shield - Use after target blocks<br>
---<br>
As far as I (and all I have asked) this style is broken. It does not work after you block (like Sword and Hammer's block styles), and I have never been able to execute it after being blocked by another player in RvR (this is hard to test outside RvR as I have yet to find a mob that blocks me). I have asked on both VNBoards and other sites and have yet to find anyone who have used this style.<br>
<br>
A style that requires us to block the opponent would be a better style here (not as much for skalds as we do not use shield all that much, but for those warriors and thanes that use axe and shield)<br>
---<br>
<br>
(25) Raider - Use after Pillager<br>
---<br>
This style has a medium PENALTY to hit making the Pillager&gt;Raider combo less attractive when attacking higher level mobs (as in grouping) and in RvR (you really don't want to miss in RvR). Often using this chain in groups you will connect with Pillager (which is an endurance hog) and miss with Raider (which has the low endurance usage). If this style (and the chain) is to be viable after axe users get (29) Havoc, Raider needs to have a bonus to hit instead of penalty.<br>
---<br>
<br>
(44) Arctic Rift - Use after Evernight.<br>
---<br>
This is the highest style many skalds will reach and is utterly useless as we will never get the prerequisite style off. As this is a high level style, a hefty damage or a stun would be nice.<br>
---<br>
<br>
These are the styles I would like to see some changes to as they constitute a large part of our higher level styles for nothing.<br>
<br>
